          <h2 class="section-header">How It Works</h2>
          <p>Made from low-cost, resilient aluminum reflectors, the concentrator is mounted on a tracker which rests on a steel mast. The FOCUS 250 parabolic reflector dish follows the sun on two axes throughout the day, always maximizing capture of solar radiation. The solar radiation is reflected off the concentrator onto a central receiver, heating a circulating thermal fluid. The heated fluid then passes through a heat exchanger to create high temperature steam, or other high temperature and enthalpy fluids which can be used for a wide variety of applications.</p>
